oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Photograph of Pinewood
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The church is pictured on the left. A cotton factory is also pictured on the middle right area of the picture, near the smokestack. Pinewood Mansion is on the right. On the left is the cotton gin; brick was also manufactured at Pinewood. The camera in this image would have been facing the north. The photograph came from a person in Hohenwald, Tenn. See Tennessee Historical Quarterly 27, No. 1, Spring 1968, Pinewood article.
